headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 30 points and Washington beat the Detroit Pistons 118-104 on Saturday in a matchup of the NBA's worst teams for Brian Keefe’s first victory in two games as the Wizards' interim coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Pistons in matchup of NBA’s worst teams for Keefe’s 1st win as interim coach

headlines.description: — Rolling since they got OG Anunoby, the New York Knicks might have to keep it up without Julius Randle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 32 points, Knicks win 6th straight and send Heat to 6th loss in a row, 125-109

headlines.description: — This matinee was no marquee, not with one of its co-stars missing again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets fend off gritty 76ers 111-105 as Embiid sits out for 4th consecutive time in Denver

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 37 points and the Brooklyn Nets outlasted the Houston Rockets 106-104 on Saturday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 37 points, Nets hold off Rockets 106-104

headlines.description: — The Clippers were embarrassed on their home court the first time they faced the Celtics.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers win their 5th straight, 115-96 over Celtics. It was just Boston's 2nd home loss

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 33 points and 12 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the Charlotte Hornets 134-122 on Saturday night for their 11th victory in 15 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 33, Jazz build 36-point lead in 134-122 victory over Hornets

headlines.description: — Doc Rivers will take over a Milwaukee Bucks team that's coming off one of its most dominant performances of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo leads balanced attack as Bucks trounce Pelicans 141-117

headlines.description: — Back and forth they went, one-upping the other, two of the greatest to ever play each believing he could will his team to win. Stepback 3s, fadeaway jumpers, drives and dishes. Two overtimes.
